column5: Well, they were at the wrong camp LOL!  From what I've heard they may film at Eddie's camp next spring. I'm sure they'll do better.
Most were of good size,and I believe they they had a 50"er as well. Hard to believe there are better places then there.
I was just joking. Pym is a great camp.    Not sure yet, although I'd definitely like too.
Based on the reports I've read, and the consequent stains on my pants...Pym and Eddie's are both good enough for me
Richter isn't part of this equation Gord.
Depends as in diapers, "consequent stains on my pants" oh nevermind my poor attempt at humour Mike!!!
